From aad23c657a2139095c8e6417dc8060f0a9bf09cf Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: reardonia <2925104+reardonia@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Fri, 8 May 2026 10:01:54 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 18/24] VAAPI/GLES: hardware decode for packed 4:2:2 (Y210,
 Y212, Y216)

Cover HEVC Main422_10 and Main422_12 on GBM + GLES by wiring up the
packed surface fourccs Intel iHD produces: Y210 (10-bit), Y212
(12-bit), Y216 (16-bit storage).

Shader: SHADER_Y210 added to EShaderFormat. The XBMC_Y210 branch in
gles_yuv2rgb_basic.frag samples GL_RGBA16 (which Mesa maps Y210/Y212/
Y216 to) with channel mapping RGBA -> Y0, Cb, Y1, Cr and the YUY2-style
two-luma-one-chroma-pair interpolation in 16-bit width.

kVaFormatTable extends with Y210, Y212, Y216 entries; the probe
iterates the table and Adds the matching AVPixelFormat for each fourcc
that passes a TestEsh round trip.

CVaapi2Texture::Map handles num_layers == 1 (single-plane packed
formats); the layer is bound to m_y and the shader decodes the packed
layout.

Surface fourcc plumbing: CVaapiConfig gains a pixelFormat field set in
ConfigVAAPI alongside vaCreateSurfaces. CVaapiProcessedPicture gains a
fourcc field; COutput::ProcessPicture stamps it from
m_config.pixelFormat. CRendererVAAPIGLES::Configure captures
procPic.fourcc into m_vaapiFourcc; GetShaderFormat dispatches per
fourcc to NV12_RRG (semi-planar 4:2:0) or Y210 (packed 10/12/16-bit
4:2:2). UploadTexture halves planes[0].texwidth (ceiling for odd
widths) and sets pixpertex_x = 2 for the packed-422 fourccs to match
the LinuxRendererGLES YUYV path.

CDecoder::Open dispatches AV_PROFILE_HEVC_REXT to HEVCMain422_10 /
HEVCMain422_12 when the pix_fmt is 4:2:2 and the bit-depth class is
supported in caps. CDecoder::ConfigVAAPI accepts VA_RT_FORMAT_YUV422_10
/ YUV422_12 and selects Y210 for 10-bit, Y212 (with Y216 fallback) for
12-bit.
